      <div class="body">
        <div class="cardcontainer">

          <!-- Card 1 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Power of Protein</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/proteinfood.jpg" alt="Protein Foods" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Protein-Rich Foods</h3>
                <p>Protein builds and repairs muscle, supports immune function, and keeps you fuller for longer. Great sources: chicken, fish, eggs, lentils, beans, and tofu.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 2 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Importance of Hydration</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/water.jpg" alt="Water" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Stay Hydrated</h3>
                <p>Water regulates body temperature, aids digestion, and transports nutrients. Drinking enough water prevents fatigue and supports workout recovery.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 3 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Healthy Carbohydrates</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/carbs.jpg" alt="Carbs" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Fuel for Energy</h3>
                <p>Whole grains, oats, sweet potatoes, and fruits provide complex carbs that fuel your body, especially before workouts. Avoid refined sugar and processed carbs.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 4 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Healthy Fats Matter</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/healthyfats.jpg" alt="Healthy Fats" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Good Fats vs Bad Fats</h3>
                <p>Omega-3 fatty acids from salmon, walnuts, and flaxseeds improve heart health. Use olive oil instead of hydrogenated oils. Say no to deep-fried foods.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 5 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Fiber for Digestion</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/fibers.jpg" alt="Fiber foods" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Gut Health</h3>
                <p>Fruits, vegetables, and whole grains are rich in fiber. It aids digestion, prevents constipation, and keeps you feeling light and active.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 6 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Vitamins & Minerals</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/vitamins.jpg" alt="Vitamins" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Micronutrients</h3>
                <p>Leafy greens, fruits, and nuts provide essential vitamins and minerals that strengthen immunity and enhance energy production.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 7 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Meal Timing</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/mealtiming.jpg" alt="Meal Timing" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>When You Eat Matters</h3>
                <p>Eating small, balanced meals every 3â€“4 hours stabilizes blood sugar and keeps energy levels steady. Never skip breakfast!</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 8 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Superfoods</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/superfoods.jpg" alt="Superfoods" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Boost Your Health</h3>
                <p>Blueberries, chia seeds, spinach, and green tea are nutrient-dense foods that fight inflammation and support overall wellness.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 9 -->
          <div class="card">
            <h1>Balanced Diet</h1>
            <div class="contentcontainer">
              <div class="images">
                <img src="../images/balanced.jpg" alt="Balanced Diet" />
              </div>
              <div class="content">
                <h3>Mix It Right</h3>
                <p>A healthy plate should include proteins, carbs, fats, and fiber in balanced proportions. Consistency is key for long-term health.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
